A.Key Characteristics

Important properties of FormRecord:

1.Supports dynamic keys

2.Stores FormControl objects

3.Structure is object-based

4.Provides runtime flexibility

5.Works with typed reactive forms

6.Supports validators and form state management


B.Core Operations Supported

FormRecord supports all major control container operations.

Main operations include:

1.Add control dynamically

2.Remove existing control

3.Replace existing control

4.Check if control exists

5.Retrieve specific control

6.Update values

7.Reset form state

These operations allow developers to manage dynamic form structures efficiently.


C.Nested FormRecord

FormRecord can be nested inside other form containers.

Possible nesting structures include:

FormGroup → FormRecord

FormRecord → FormGroup

FormRecord → FormRecord

This allows developers to build complex dynamic form hierarchies.

